laboratory_examinations.findings: Revealed a lumbosacral myelomeningocele sac, tethered terminal filum, and an associated syringohydromyelic cavity above the thoracic SCM.
Revealed the thoracic diastematomyelic median osseous septum in detail, indicating a Type I SCM.

laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: Plain Radiographs of the Spinal Column
laboratory_examinations.findings: Demonstrated posterior fusion defects at T9–11, L4–5, and S-1 together with partial sacral agenesis and costal abnormalities.
